According to RDT Token Flow and Amazon SP-API Java SDK I want to point to [this official example workflow][1]. 

Unfortunately the use of 
`ordersApi.getApiClient().addDefaultHeader(&quot;x-amz-access-token&quot;, token);`
is broken in the ApiClient provided by Amazon and needs some custom adjustment to make it work.

If the request is only signed by LwaAuthorizationSigner when x-amz-access-token is missing, fixes the flow for me. Compare this [PR][2]

Change ApiClient.java like this:

    -        request = lwaAuthorizationSigner.sign(request);
    +        if (!defaultHeaderMap.containsKey(&quot;x-amz-access-token&quot;)) {
    +            request = lwaAuthorizationSigner.sign(request);
    +        }


